    <h1>Guide Management in LEGO HubLab 🐕‍🦺</h1>

    <pre class="ascii-art">
      _____
     /     \    LEGO HubLab
    /       \   Guide Management
   /  /\ /\  \  System
  /  /  V  \  \ 
 /  /       \  \
/  /  GUIDE  \  \
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    </pre>

    <h2>1. Accessing the Maintenance Page</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    +----------------+
    |   Password:    |
    |  ************  |
    |   [  Login  ]  |
    +----------------+
    </pre>
    <p>Navigate to <code>yourdomain.com/maintenance.html</code> and enter the secure password.</p>

    <h2>2. Adding a New Guide</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    +-------------------+
    | [+] Add New Guide |
    +-------------------+
          |
          v
    +-------------------+
    | Title: [        ] |
    | Lang:  [Select v] |
    | Content:          |
    | +---------------+ |
    | |               | |
    | |    Markdown   | |
    | |     Editor    | |
    | |               | |
    | +---------------+ |
    | [  Save Guide   ] |
    +-------------------+
    </pre>
    <ol>
        <li>Click "Add New Guide" button</li>
        <li>Enter the guide title</li>
        <li>Select the language (en, he, ar, ru)</li>
        <li>Write your guide content in Markdown format</li>
        <li>Click "Save Guide" to add it to the system</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>3. Editing Existing Guides</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    +--------------------+
    | Guide List         |
    |                    |
    | 1. Lab Safety   [E]|
    | 2. PCR Tech     [E]|
    | 3. Data Vis     [E]|
    |        ...         |
    +--------------------+
          |
          v
    +--------------------+
    | Edit Guide         |
    |                    |
    | Title: [        ]  |
    | Lang:  [Select v]  |
    | Content:           |
    | +----------------+ |
    | |                | |
    | |    Markdown    | |
    | |     Editor     | |
    | |                | |
    | +----------------+ |
    | [  Update Guide  ] |
    +--------------------+
    </pre>
    <ol>
        <li>Find the guide you want to edit in the list</li>
        <li>Click the [E] button next to the guide title</li>
        <li>Modify the title, language, or content as needed</li>
        <li>Click "Update Guide" to save changes</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>4. Managing Guide Hierarchy</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    Root
    ├── Anesthesia
    │   ├── Anatomy
    │   ├── Physiology
    │   └── Pharmacology
    ├── Lab
    │   ├── Safety
    │   └── Techniques
    └── Statistics
        ├── Basics
        └── Advanced
    </pre>
    <p>Use the drag-and-drop interface to reorganize guides:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Drag a guide to change its position</li>
        <li>Drop it onto another guide to make it a sub-guide</li>
        <li>Drop it between guides to reorder</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Adding ASCII Art to Guides</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    Markdown:
    ```ascii
      _____
     /     \
    /  Lab  \
   /  Safety \
  /___________\
    ```
    </pre>
    <p>Use triple backticks with 'ascii' to add ASCII art to your guides.</p>

    <h2>6. Creating Interactive Elements</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    +-------------------+
    | [?] Quiz Question |
    +-------------------+
    | ( ) Option A      |
    | ( ) Option B      |
    | ( ) Option C      |
    | [    Submit    ]  |
    +-------------------+
    </pre>
    <p>Use special markdown syntax for quizzes and interactive elements:</p>
    <pre><code>
    ???question "What is the boiling point of water?"
    [ ] 0°C
    [x] 100°C
    [ ] 50°C
    ???
    </code></pre>

    <h2>7. Localizing Guides</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    EN -----> [Translate] -----> HE
    |                            |
    v                            v
    AR <---- [Translate] <----- RU
    </pre>
    <p>For each guide:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Create versions in all supported languages (en, he, ar, ru)</li>
        <li>Use the same file name with language suffix (e.g., lab-safety-en.html, lab-safety-he.html)</li>
        <li>Ensure proper RTL formatting for Hebrew and Arabic versions</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>8. Publishing and Updating</h2>
    <pre class="ascii-art">
    [Draft] ---> [Review] ---> [Publish]
      ^                           |
      |                           |
      +---------------------------+
             [Update]
    </pre>
    <p>Guide lifecycle:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Create or edit guide (Draft stage)</li>
        <li>Submit for review</li>
        <li>Publish when approved</li>
        <li>Update as needed, returning to Draft stage</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="lego-block">
        <h3>LEGO HubLab Tip</h3>
        <p>Think of each guide as a unique LEGO brick. The maintenance page is your sorting tray, helping you organize and connect these bricks into a comprehensive knowledge structure!</p>
    </div>

